{{Lunisolar March}} '''March 24''' is the 24th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Tomobiki|ja|友引|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Daiji|ja|大治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1126]] {{ill|April 18|ja|4月18日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Fudoki ceremony for the gold hall and triple pagoda of 【Chūson-ji|中尊寺】 was held. * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Battle of Dan-no-ura took place, leading to the extinction of the Taira clan. * [[Ōnin]] 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1468]] {{ill|April 16|ja|4月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – At [[Kata Daiseki|堅田大責]], Enryaku-ji burned the town of Kata in Ōmi Province. * {{ill|Tenmei|ja|天明|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1784]] {{ill|May 13|ja|5月13日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – A young retainer of Tanuma Ittetsu, named Tanuma Itchi, was slain in the palace; he died on the 2nd day of the old month. * {{ill|Kōka|ja|弘化|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1847]] {{ill|May 7|ja|5月7日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – An earthquake struck at Nagano near 【Zenko-ji|善光寺】, with reported casualties of 8,000–12,000. == Births ==
== Deaths == * {{ill|Engi|ja|延喜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[910]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Takako|ja|藤原高子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a consort of Emperor Seiwa and mother of Emperor Yōzei (born [[842]]). * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Andoku (【安徳天皇】), the 81st Emperor of Japan (born [[1178]]). * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Heiji Toki-shi|ja|平時子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, wife of Taira no Kiyomori and grandmother of Emperor Andoku. * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Taira no Chimisori|ja|平知盛|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and son of Taira no Kiyomori (born [[1152]]). * {{ill|Kennin|ja|建仁|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1201]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and governor of Shimōsa (born [[1118]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap March) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1830]] {{ill|May 16|ja|5月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ishikawa Masamune|ja|石川雅望|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar (born [[1753]]).
