== Deaths == * {{ill|Engi|ja|延喜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[910]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Takako|ja|藤原高子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a consort of Emperor Seiwa and mother of Emperor Yōzei (born [[842]]). * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – Emperor Andoku (【安徳天皇】), the 81st Emperor of Japan (born [[1178]]). * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Heiji Toki-shi|ja|平時子|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, wife of Taira no Kiyomori and grandmother of Emperor Andoku. * {{ill|Bunchi|ja|文治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1185]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Taira no Chimisori|ja|平知盛|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and son of Taira no Kiyomori (born [[1152]]). * {{ill|Kennin|ja|建仁|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1201]] {{ill|April 28|ja|4月28日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a military commander and governor of Shimōsa (born [[1118]]). * {{ill|Tenpō|ja|天保|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year (leap March) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1830]] {{ill|May 16|ja|5月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Ishikawa Masamune|ja|石川雅望|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, a Kokugaku scholar (born [[1753]]).
