== Deaths == * [[:en:Engi (era)|Engi]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:910|910]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – {{ill|Fujiwara Takako|ja|藤原高子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Takako|qq=}}, a consort of Emperor Seiwa and mother of Emperor Yōzei (born [[:en:842|842]]). * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Emperor Andoku (【安徳天皇】), the 81st Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1178|1178]]). * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tokiko|Heiji Toki-shi]], wife of Taira no Kiyomori and grandmother of Emperor Andoku. * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tomomori|Taira no Chimisori]], a military commander and son of Taira no Kiyomori (born [[:en:1152|1152]]). * [[:en:Kennin|Kennin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1201|1201]] [[:en:April 28|April 28]]) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiba Tsunetane|qq=}}, a military commander and governor of Shimōsa (born [[:en:1118|1118]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 1st year (leap March) ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1830|1830]] [[:en:May 16|May 16]]) – [[:en:Ishikawa Masamochi|Ishikawa Masamune]], a Kokugaku scholar (born [[:en:1753|1753]]).
