== Events == * {{ill|Daiji|ja|大治|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daiji|qq=|1=Daiji|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q10936305}} 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1126|1126]] [[:en:April 18|April 18]]) – The Fudoki ceremony for the gold hall and triple pagoda of 【Chūson-ji|中尊寺】 was held. * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – The Battle of Dan-no-ura took place, leading to the extinction of the Taira clan. * [[:en:Ōnin|Ōnin]] 2nd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1468|1468]] [[:en:April 16|April 16]]) – At [[Kata Daiseki|堅田大責]], Enryaku-ji burned the town of Kata in Ōmi Province. * [[:en:Tenmei|Tenmei]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1784|1784]] [[:en:May 13|May 13]]) – A young retainer of Tanuma Ittetsu, named Tanuma Itchi, was slain in the palace; he died on the 2nd day of the old month. * [[:en:Kōka|Kōka]] 4th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1847|1847]] [[:en:May 7|May 7]]) – An earthquake struck at Nagano near 【Zenko-ji|善光寺】, with reported casualties of 8,000–12,000. == Births ==
== Deaths == * [[:en:Engi (era)|Engi]] 10th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:910|910]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – {{ill|Fujiwara Takako|ja|藤原高子|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Takako|qq=|1=Fujiwara no Takaiko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q127411}}, a consort of Emperor Seiwa and mother of Emperor Yōzei (born [[:en:842|842]]). * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – Emperor Andoku (【安徳天皇】), the 81st Emperor of Japan (born [[:en:1178|1178]]). * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tokiko|Heiji Toki-shi]], wife of Taira no Kiyomori and grandmother of Emperor Andoku. * [[:en:Bunji (era)|Bunchi]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1185|1185]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – [[:en:Taira no Tomomori|Taira no Chimisori]], a military commander and son of Taira no Kiyomori (born [[:en:1152|1152]]). * [[:en:Kennin|Kennin]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1201|1201]] [[:en:April 28|April 28]]) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiba Tsunetane|qq=|1=Chiba Tsunetane|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11406057}}, a military commander and governor of Shimōsa (born [[:en:1118|1118]]). * [[:en:Tenpō|Tenpō]] 1st year (leap March) ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[:en:1830|1830]] [[:en:May 16|May 16]]) – [[:en:Ishikawa Masamochi|Ishikawa Masamune]], a Kokugaku scholar (born [[:en:1753|1753]]).
