== Events == * {{ill|Daiji|ja|大治|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Daiji|1=Q10936305|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q10936305}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1126|en|1126|qid=Q30114|lt=1126|1=1126}} {{ill|April 18|en|April 18|qid=Q2521|lt=April 18|1=April 18}}) – The Fudoki ceremony for the gold hall and triple pagoda of 【Chūson-ji|中尊寺】 was held. * {{ill|Bunji (era)|en|Bunji (era)|qid=Q1194415|lt=Bunchi|1=Bunji (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1185|en|1185|qid=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – The Battle of Dan-no-ura took place, leading to the extinction of the Taira clan. * {{ill|Ōnin|en|Ōnin|qid=Q1143903|lt=Ōnin|1=Ōnin}} 2nd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1468|en|1468|qid=Q6564|lt=1468|1=1468}} {{ill|April 16|en|April 16|qid=Q2519|lt=April 16|1=April 16}}) – At [[Kata Daiseki|堅田大責]], Enryaku-ji burned the town of Kata in Ōmi Province. * {{ill|Tenmei|en|Tenmei|qid=Q1194121|lt=Tenmei|1=Tenmei}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1784|en|1784|qid=Q7752|lt=1784|1=1784}} {{ill|May 13|en|May 13|qid=Q2560|lt=May 13|1=May 13}}) – A young retainer of Tanuma Ittetsu, named Tanuma Itchi, was slain in the palace; he died on the 2nd day of the old month. * {{ill|Kōka|en|Kōka|qid=Q1325317|lt=Kōka|1=Kōka}} 4th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1847|en|1847|qid=Q7644|lt=1847|1=1847}} {{ill|May 7|en|May 7|qid=Q2553|lt=May 7|1=May 7}}) – An earthquake struck at Nagano near 【Zenko-ji|善光寺】, with reported casualties of 8,000–12,000. == Births ==
== Deaths == * {{ill|Engi (era)|en|Engi (era)|qid=Q1374325|lt=Engi|1=Engi (era)}} 10th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|910|en|910|qid=Q30362|lt=910|1=910}} {{ill|May 6|en|May 6|qid=Q2552|lt=May 6|1=May 6}}) – {{ill|Fujiwara Takako|ja|藤原高子|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujiwara Takako|1=Fujiwara no Takaiko|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q127411}}, a consort of Emperor Seiwa and mother of Emperor Yōzei (born {{ill|842|en|842|qid=Q24730|lt=842|1=842}}). * {{ill|Bunji (era)|en|Bunji (era)|qid=Q1194415|lt=Bunchi|1=Bunji (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1185|en|1185|qid=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – Emperor Andoku (【安徳天皇】), the 81st Emperor of Japan (born {{ill|1178|en|1178|qid=Q19696|lt=1178|1=1178}}). * {{ill|Bunji (era)|en|Bunji (era)|qid=Q1194415|lt=Bunchi|1=Bunji (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1185|en|1185|qid=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – {{ill|Taira no Tokiko|en|Taira no Tokiko|qid=Q3379244|lt=Heiji Toki-shi|1=Taira no Tokiko}}, wife of Taira no Kiyomori and grandmother of Emperor Andoku. * {{ill|Bunji (era)|en|Bunji (era)|qid=Q1194415|lt=Bunchi|1=Bunji (era)}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1185|en|1185|qid=Q19729|lt=1185|1=1185}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – {{ill|Taira no Tomomori|en|Taira no Tomomori|qid=Q736706|lt=Taira no Chimisori|1=Taira no Tomomori}}, a military commander and son of Taira no Kiyomori (born {{ill|1152|en|1152|qid=Q19645|lt=1152|1=1152}}). * {{ill|Kennin|en|Kennin|qid=Q1195433|lt=Kennin|1=Kennin}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1201|en|1201|qid=Q5225|lt=1201|1=1201}} {{ill|April 28|en|April 28|qid=Q2534|lt=April 28|1=April 28}}) – {{ill|Chiba Tsunetane|ja|千葉常胤|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Chiba Tsunetane|1=Chiba Tsunetane|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11406057}}, a military commander and governor of Shimōsa (born {{ill|1118|en|1118|qid=Q19539|lt=1118|1=1118}}). * {{ill|Tenpō|en|Tenpō|qid=Q1369045|lt=Tenpō|1=Tenpō}} 1st year (leap March) ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1830|en|1830|qid=Q7576|lt=1830|1=1830}} {{ill|May 16|en|May 16|qid=Q2574|lt=May 16|1=May 16}}) – {{ill|Ishikawa Masamochi|en|Ishikawa Masamochi|qid=Q6535184|lt=Ishikawa Masamune|1=Ishikawa Masamochi}}, a Kokugaku scholar (born {{ill|1753|en|1753|qid=Q7621|lt=1753|1=1753}}).
